## ❗ Problem Being Solved

Reference collection is:

time-consuming (30–60 min per scene)
inconsistent across artists
duplicated across team members

**Pain points addressed**:

- Slow manual research
- Lack of standardised references
- Inconsistent visual direction

---

## ⚡ Automation Potential

**Level: High**

| Dimension | Assessment |
|-----------|------------|
| Repetitiveness | Very high — same format needed every time |
| Data availability | Input comes directly from P02 approved location brief |
| Human judgment needed | High — Artist confirms relevance; art director spot-checks before layout begins |
| Integration possibility | Output can feed into shared reference board tools such as PureRef or Milanote |
| Estimated time saving | ~80% — from 1–3 hrs to 15–20 min per location |

**Human-in-the-loop role:** Artists review and select references; AI provides structured starting point.
---

## ⚠️ Risks and Limitations

| Risk | Level | Mitigation |
|------|-------|------------|
| AI introduces elements not in scene and include AI generated images | **High** | Grounding constraint: "using ONLY the information provided below" + "do not infer or assume" |
| Output too generic | Medium | "Insufficient data — follow-up required" fallback built into prompt |
| Missing details due to limited input | **High** | Governance policy: manager sign-off is mandatory before submission. Prompt output is marked as DRAFT. |
| Over-reliance on AI suggestions | **High** | Legal review required for any report involving injury, significant property damage, or potential litigation |

**Overall risk rating: MEDIUM** — controlled through strict grounding + human validation

